(42, 6, 39, 40, 23, 16, 26, NULL, 'Blind Guides and Their Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of blindness in spiritual leadership. Luke 6:39 poses a rhetorical question about the blind leading the blind, while Matthew 23:16-26 directly addresses the Pharisees as ''blind guides,'' highlighting their misguided teachings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 39, 54, 6, 3, 5, 'Can the blind lead the blind?', 'Blind Leading the Blind', 'This connection highlights the danger of false teaching, as both passages warn against those who lack understanding and lead others astray. The metaphor of the blind leading the blind in Luke reflects the consequences of corrupt minds in 1 Timothy.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 39, 23, 9, 16, 16, 'blind lead the blind', 'Blind Leaders and Their Followers', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of misguided leadership. Luke''s metaphor of the blind leading the blind parallels Isaiah''s warning about leaders causing their people to err.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
