(42, 6, 40, 43, 13, 16, 16, NULL, 'Discipleship and Servanthood', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between a master and his disciple or servant, highlighting that neither is greater than the other. This connection underscores the principle of humility and the expectation of following one''s leader.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 40, 40, 10, 24, 25, 'The disciple is not above his master', 'Discipleship and Mastery Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between a disciple and their master, stating that a disciple is not above their master. This connection highlights the expectation that disciples will be like their master, reinforcing the theme of discipleship.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 40, 43, 15, 20, 20, NULL, 'Discipleship and Persecution', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between a master and his disciple or servant, highlighting that the disciple or servant is not above their master. This connection illustrates the expectation of shared experiences, including persecution, between Jesus and his followers.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 40, 40, 23, 15, 15, 'the disciple is not above his master', 'Discipleship and Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the impact of a teacher on their followers. Luke highlights that a disciple becomes like their master, while Matthew warns that the Pharisees make their proselytes worse than themselves.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
