(42, 6, 41, 59, 1, 24, 24, 'beholdest thou the mote', 'Self-Reflection and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of self-awareness and the tendency to overlook one''s own faults while judging others. Luke 6:41 highlights the failure to see one''s own ''beam,'' while James 1:24 discusses forgetting one''s own reflection, suggesting a parallel in the theme of self-examination.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 6, 41, 45, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'Judgment and Self-Reflection', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of judging others while ignoring one''s own faults. Luke highlights the hypocrisy of noticing a ''mote'' in another''s eye, while Romans points out that judging others leads to self-condemnation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
