(42, 6, 42, 40, 23, 13, 15, 'hypocrite, cast out first the beam', 'Hypocrisy and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of hypocrisy, where individuals are criticized for failing to address their own faults before judging others. The call to remove the ''beam'' from one''s own eye in Luke parallels the condemnation of the Pharisees'' actions in Matthew, highlighting their failure to lead by example.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
